During a meeting about education and the reopening of schools, President Trump and Vice President Pence discussed the importance of opening schools for in-person learning. They emphasized the need for schools to have resources and guidance to safely reopen, and called on Congress to appropriate additional funding for this purpose. They also highlighted the negative consequences of keeping students out of school, including academic setbacks and the loss of counseling and other support services. Various parents and educators shared their experiences and concerns about virtual learning and expressed their desire for students to return to in-person instruction. The President and Vice President also mentioned the concept of school choice and the idea of having funding follow the student. The meeting concluded with remarks from Dr. Scott Atlas, an expert from Stanford, who emphasized the low risk of COVID-19 for children and the importance of getting kids back to school safely.